  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Geth is painfully slow on non SSD drives. Syncing speed is 1 block per 5 sec.\r\nAlso leveldb, used by geth, has serious write amplification problems (essentially an SSD killer) when the same data is written tens of times in process of numerous compactions.\r\nAre other DBs considered for geth? The current one seem to be not well suited neither for HDD (too slow) nor for SSD (kills it quickly). Which might be a bigger problem when chain data keeps growing.",
