    "body": "It means it is a known serious bug. \r\n\r\nI started with geth on 27-may on 8-may I stuck at block number 2468707, I save that data for future use (69.5GB). I was syncing only 10 hours daily. I shoved in different fora but can't get any relevant information but one that you should use --fast mode. I thought I should give a try. After running geth for continuous 10 days I have to stopped it yesterday (see #14647). At last I export from geth (2468707) and import in parity and in 6 hours I have the best block.\r\n\r\nAs, I am not a geek, you may understand my frustration.\r\n\r\nMy opinion, do not use geth in fast mode.",
